33:<I feel the same way. After I do the lesson and before I call a group, I walk around and watch the student's do their independent work. I try to pull students who I noticed were struggling on the current lesson first.  This is not the same set of students every time. Then I try to call over as many students as I can before the " exit ticket time.  I was not sure if this was the right way to do it. But if there are more than 5 students who are struggling I may assign a mentor. Now I am questioning the way I do it. I feel like I am grouping them without the title of the group.???  :( The students who do their independent work are able to grade their own work with the answer key, with a different color pen and then are asked to hand it in before they can work on center work.  The centers are student choices.  I have a tick tac toe board every week with different tasks they can accomplish. It ranges from "review" work to Challenge activities.  If the student wants to get a tic tac toe for the week they HAVE TO COMPLETE a challenge activity. This can be done with a buddy of their choice or independently.  At the end of the week all students have to make one tic tac toe for "credit" and then if they wanted to try to get more than one tic tac toe it is worth more.  :)  It become as a fun game for my students and they have the ability to work at a level of their choice and be challenged.>
