48:<Method 1:

let x=number of rocks in A

Total number of rocks = A plus B plus C

14=x+(2+x)+4x

so

14=6x+2, and finally x=2.

so A has 2, B has 4, C has 8


Method 2:

let x=number of rocks in B

Total number of rocks = A plus B plus C

14=(x-2)+(x)+(4(x-2))

so

14=6x-10, finally x=4

so A has 2, B has 4, C has 8


Method 3:

let x=number of rocks in C

Total number of rocks = A plus B plus C

14=(0.25x)+(0.25x+2)+(x)

so

14=1.5x+2, finally  x=8

so A has 2, B has 4, C has 8>
