63:<As a teacher in a gifted education program - I do have a concern about telling teachers that it is best to used "mixed groups" as I already see others making comments about using the 'higher ability' students to guide the others.  What happens is that the higher ability students get stuck "pulling the others along" and aren't given the opportunity to learn at their own pace... to soar!

I agree that teachers often teach - not to the middle of the group but sometimes to the "least common denominator" :(  Unfortunately leaving so many of the students not being challenged!

I would note that although students in our program have to 'qualify' for enrollment, we do have students with a range of abilities! I would never "track" them... we are peers and we work together!  I have the expectation that ALL of my students will be wildly successful - and they generally are...>
